The paper discusses the use of ontology for knowledge sharing and communication in complex enterprise systems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also focuses on the semantic interpretation of data published on the web, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper proposes a framework for B2C transactions, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and database management (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses the interoperability and integration of transactions across different business domains, which is related to cybersecurity (cs.CY).
